  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "ImageMagick security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for ImageMagick is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Use ImageMagick to create, edit, compose, or convert bitmap images. It can read and write images in a variety of formats (over 200) including PNG, JPEG, GIF, HEIC, TIFF, DPX, EXR, WebP, Postscript, PDF, and SVG. Use ImageMagick to resize, flip, mirror, rotate, distort, shear and transform images, adjust image colors, apply various special effects, or draw text, lines, polygons, ellipses and BÃ©zier curves.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nImageMagick is a software suite to create, edit, compose, or convert bitmap images. ImageMagick versions prior to 7.1.2-8 are vulnerable to denial-of-service due to unsigned integer underflow and division-by-zero in the CLAHEImage function. When tile width or height is zero, unsigned underflow occurs in pointer arithmetic, leading to out-of-bounds memory access, and division-by-zero causes immediate crashes. This issue has been patched in version 7.1.2-8.(CVE-2025-62594)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for ImageMagick is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of medium. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Medium",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "ImageMagick",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
